				<br>
				A few weeks ago, while reading Michael Pollan's In Defense of Food, I started perusing the ingredient lists on the back of the various food products that live in our kitchen. Honey Nut Cheerios (healthy, right?):  corn syrup solids, tripotassium phosphate, guar gum, and assorted other non-oat-or-nut-related ingredients......
The food in my food suddenly seemed disturbingly un-foody.

So I unpacked the cupboard full of pita chips and Cheerios, canned soup,egg substitute and fifty-ingredient bread... They are being replaced, slowly but surely, with whole foods and with mostly plants: quinoa, wild rice, black beans, Bhutanese red rice, lentils, split peas, chickpeas, leafy greens, rainbow carrots, potatoes, actual eggs, peaches, melons, figs, nuts, bread with pronounceable ingredients.

The only problem is, now I have to figure out how to cook all this stuff.
